{
  "texts": [
    "Contrary to our prediction, participants were disproportionately likely to identify the computer passages as being computer-generated (Mdn = 0.30) relative to the null hypothesis of 0.50 (i.e., chance performance), z = -12.51, p < 0.001.",
    "The effect size was large (r = -0.74).",
    "Indeed, 80.1% of the participants made correct identifications more than half the time.",
    "A finer-grained analysis was employed to extend our hypothesis test to each of the 10 accuracy judgments individually.",
    "We constructed a set of one-sample binomials, using a Bonferroni correction for multiple tests (alpha = 0.005)."
  ]
}